EFF Tshwane Regional Chairperson Moafrika Mabogwana speaks to eNCA. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The EFF wants Tshwane Mayor, Stevens Mokgalapa, out. The red berets have submitted an urgent motion of no confidence against Mokgalapa. The EFF says the city has been limping from one disaster to another since he took over. The party's Regional Chairperson Moafrika Mabogwana says the mayor has breached the oath of office. WATCH: Tshwane mayor chose to take special leave "We are speaking about the issue of maladministration and corruption. When he came into office he promised the people of Hammanskraal clean water. The Mayor has lied. He has breached the oath of office and as a result, he is not fit to be a mayor of Tshwane." The embattled mayor has been embroiled in a sex scandal in the city's offices with Transport MMC, Sheila Senkubuge. WATCH: DA to probe Tshwane mayor amid sex scandal The DA says its Federal Legal Commission will investigate and the two will get a chance to give their version of events. Mokgalapa and Senkubuge have elected to take leave until the probe is over. Watch the full interview with the EFF's Regional Chairperson Moafrika Mabogwana above.